description._content: Description: Ocean Island, or Banaba, from the south looking into Home Bay. Location: Ocean Island, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Description: A view of Sydney, or Solomon's Point, the south east point of the island. On the shore may be seen the native village of Uma; in the foreground is one of the famous deep sea mooring buoys of the British Phosphate Commissioners. Location: Ocean Island, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/642. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
